    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-04-19T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-04-19T23:00:00-05:00" n="699"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d699">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.6363/3532: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-04-19T22:00:00-06:00"
                            >April 19, 1938—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 19—9:14 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>137. <hi rend="italic">Amparo</hi> on behalf of some of the smaller oil companies
                    on the ground the expropriation decree established monopoly and was <pb
                        facs="0758" n="749" xml:id="pg_749"/> therefore in violation of article 28
                    of the Constitution has been denied. This request for <hi rend="italic"
                        >amparo</hi> was in addition to those mentioned in the Embassy’s despatch
                    6496 of April 15.<note n="4" xml:id="d699fn4">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Congress has now approved the 100 million peso bond issue and steps are being
                    taken now to secure subscriptions. It is said that organizations and industries
                    will be expected to subscribe. Railway Workers Council of Administration has
                    been appointed to operate national railways.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Daniels</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
